com.k2.FilesystemEntityManager

Class FemOcn

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.k2.FilesystemEntityManager.FemOcn
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FemWrapper

    public class FemOcn
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the super class of the wrapper used to persists object instances that have a storage data structure of OCN. This class is used to read the OCN from the file system without having to parse the persisted object instance data All classes whether persisted as a RAW or as an OCN are held in the file system entity managers cache in a FemWrapper instance
    Author:
    simon

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      java.lang.String hash
      Classes with a data structure of RAW do not maintain an OCN instead the MD5 hash of the file persisting the objects instance data is used to identify a mutating object
      java.lang.Integer ocn
      The Object Change Number (OCN) of the persisted object instance data The OCN starts at zero and is incremented each time an object saved is updated and if the OCN of the object when it was read doesn't match the OCN of the object in the repository a mutated object exception is thrown
